We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the following: 

The BAC to hold a pre-procurement conference for procurement of goods with an ABC of more than ₱2,000,000.00, infrastructure projects with ABC of more than ₱5,000,000.00 and consulting services with ABC of more than ₱1,000,000.00;


The BAC Chairman to see to it that prior to contract signing of infrastructure projects, require the winning bidder to submit CSHP approved by the DOLE;


The BAC Chairman to strictly comply of sending the invitation of observers within the prescribe period;



The BAC, through its BAC Secretariat, to prepare and send the Notification of Bid Submission, and ensure that the bidder receives the said document to ensure transparency and accurate representation of the bids submitted;

The BAC to ensure that all procurements made by the PE, under competitive bidding, strictly follow the proceedings and requirements of the bidding process;




The BAC to diligently carry out their responsibilities at every stage of the procurement process, ensuring that reports are meticulously prepared to accurately reflect actual dates and time of each activity; and


The Municipal Accountant to meticulously scrutinize all DVs submitted for processing, ensuring that these are completely supported with the required documents before authorizing payments, thereby substantiating the legality, validity and propriety of the transactions.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant to: 

reclassify Accounts Payable totaling ₱524,116.96 to Due to Officers and Employees;


refer to the Revised Chart of Accounts for LGUs and other pertinent issuances as regards recognition of specific accounts in the financial statements.

