5. The Property Officer submit the copy of Property Acknowledgement Receipt and Property Card of PPEs found at the station to the Accounting office for the necessary journal entries to recognize the same.

To ensure that the 20% DF is optimally utilized and monitored, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor, as Chairman of the Municipal Development Council, require the:

The Municipal Budget Officer to render a periodic update to the Municipal Mayor on the SAAOB of the 20% DF; 

The Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator to ensure the implementation of PPAs during the year and recommend to the Municipal Development Council the re-alignment of appropriations of PPAs Continuing Appropriation no longer identified as priority development PPAs;

The Municipal Engineer and other implementing offices concerned, to monitor the implementation of PPAs of the 20% DF in order to achieve the objectives of the fund; and 

Municipal Development Council, to ensure that the development projects to be funded out of the 20% DF are well-planned, as well as procurement- and implementation-ready in order to achieve the objectives of the fund.

