We recommended that Management avail of the remedies provided under COA Circular No. 2020-006 for the one-time cleansing of PPE account balances, subject to the full compliance of the requirements of Item 
Nos. 7 and 8 thereof, to address and rectify the deficiencies/lapses noted in the accounting of its PPE accounts and to ensure the fairness of its presentation in the statement of financial position.
We also reiterated our recommendation that Management:
Require the CAD to:
Closely coordinate with the IC and the CGSD for the conduct of thorough review and verification whether the PPE items worth P47,742,882.23 included in the RPCPPE are not yet taken up in the accounting records before appropriate disposition be made regarding the same;
Establish the details and composition of the PPE accounts balances lumped and labeled as beginning balances totaling P346,196,043.24;
Reclassify the recorded PPE items that did not meet the criteria for the capitalization threshold of P15,000.00 to its appropriate inventory or expense accounts;
Direct the IC, CAD and CGSD to:
Immediately conduct investigation and reconciliation on the noted disparity of P344,478,811.90 in the recorded PPE balances per lapsing schedule as against the RPCPPE; and
Verify the observed variance of P16,442,266.65 in the recorded cost of PPE items in the books as against the RPCPPE as presented in Paragraph 1.19 of this observation. Once identified, immediately effect the necessary adjustments to reconcile the same.

