In view of the above observations, we reiterated our recommendation that:
 the Bids and Awards Committee, through its BAC Secretariat observe the proper advertising and posting of the Invitation to Bid as prescribed in the Revised IRR of R.A. 9184 to encourage more participants in the bidding process and intensify the competition among them, which in turn, will ensure that the LGU will get the best possible proposals, as to quality and cost, for the project sought to be procured;
 the Municipality adhere to the governing rules on the sale of bidding documents provided in the Revised IRR of R.A. 9184;
 the members of the BAC submit justification/explanation on the noted violations and ensure that prospective bidders submit complete eligibility requirements and post the necessary bid security before they are marked as “passed” and declared as LCB;
 oblige the prospective bidders to post the required performance security prior to contract signing; and
 consider sending the BAC members to attend trainings on updates on the different provisions of the Government Procurement Law or R.A. 9184.

